lip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Moray","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Spanish: topographic name for someone who lived by a mulberry tree, <i>moral</i>, or a habitational name from any of the places called with this word. Compare   Del Moral  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Del Moral","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Antonio, Armando, Luis, Mario, Roberto, Alicia, Ana, Carlos, Engracia, Jorge, Juan Manuel.","Spanish: variant, with the preposition and definite article <i>del</i> ‘from the’, of   Moral   ‘mulberry tree’."]}]},{"name":"Flemming","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle High German <i>vlaeminc</i>. People from Flanders spread throughout Germany, as well as England, in the Middle Ages as clothmakers and dyers.","English: variant of   Fleming  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Fleming","meanings":["English: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, from Middle English <i>fleming</i>. The word reflects a Norman French form of Old French <i>flamanc</i> ‘Fleming’, from the stem <i>flam-</i> + the ancient Germanic suffix <i>-ing</i>. In the Middle Ages there was considerable commercial intercourse between England and the Netherlands, particularly in the wool trade, and many Flemish weavers and dyers settled in England. This surname is also common in south and east Scotland and in Ireland, where it is sometimes found in the Gaelicized form <b>Pléamonn</b>.","German: variant of   Flemming  , cognate with 1 above."]},{"name":"Flaming","meanings":["German (rarely <b>Fläming</b>): ethnic name for someone from Flanders, from Middle High German <i>vlaeminc</i>. See also   Flemming  .","Altered form of Dutch   Vlaming  , cognate with 1 above.","English: variant of   Fleming  , cognate with 1 above."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Flemming Freskin de Moray was born about 1107, in Holland, Netherlands, his father, Robert Flemming de Moray de Flandre, was 42 and his mother, Ida de Chiney, was 35. He had at least 1 son with Macheth McKay. He died about 1172, in Moray, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 67."},"et":{"ABT 1107–ABT 1172":"umbes 1107–umbes 1172","1107–1172":"1107–1172","1112–Female":"1112–Surnud","1152–1238":"1152–1238","1138–1203":"1138–1203","1067–1111":"1067–1111","1073–1117":"1073–1117","22 Nov 1117":"22. november 1117","1152":"1152","ABT 1107":"umbes 1107","1073":"1073","1172":"1172","ABT 1172":"umbes 1172","1107":"1107","1117":"1117","1238":"1238","1138":"1138","1203":"1203","1112":"1112","1111":"1111","1067":"1067","5 OCT 1111":"5. oktoober 1111","Belgium":"Belgia","Duffus Castle, Morayshire, Scotland":"Duffus, Elginshire, Scotland","La Crouzille, Puy-De-Dôme, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"La Crouzille, Puy-de-Dôme, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa","Duffas Castle, Morayshire, Scotland":"Moray, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Flanders, Noird Holland, Netherlands":"Holland, Madalmaad"},"fi":{"ABT 1107–ABT 1172":"noin 1107–noin 1172","1107–1172":"1107–1172","1112–Female":"1112–Kuollut","1152–1238":"1152–1238","1138–1203":"1138–1203","1067–1111":"1067–1111","1073–1117":"1073–1117","22 Nov 1117":"22. marraskuuta 1117","1152":"1152","ABT 1107":"noin 1107","1073":"1073","1172":"1172","ABT 1172":"noin 1172","1107":"1107","1117":"1117","1238":"1238","1138":"1138","1203":"1203","1112":"1112","1111":"1111","1067":"1067","5 O